Xinhua Middle East news summary at 2200 GMT, March 20 | GlobalPost
TRIPOLI -- Representatives from Libya's warring factions restarted the peace dialogue on Friday in the Moroccan city of Skhirat, in an attempt to form a unity government to solve the ongoing political crisis. (Libya-Peace talk)
SANAA, March 20 (Xinhua) -- The Islamic State (IS) claimed responsibility in an online statement for three bombing attacks in Yemen's capital Sanaa and Saada province that killed 137 people during Friday prayers.
A total of 88 people were killed and at least 100 others wounded on Friday in four bombing attacks in Yemen, local sources told Xinhua. (Yemen-IS)
DAMASCUS -- Two explosions targeted Kurdish gatherings celebrating the Nowruz festivity in Syria's northern province of al-Hasakah on Friday, killing and injuring at least 100 people, a monitoring group reported.
The twin bombings targeted civilian gatherings during the Nowruz celebrations in the al-Mufti neighborhood in this predominantly-Kurdish province, said the Syrian Observatory for Human Rights. (Syria-Blasts)
ANKARA -- Around 200 Chinese Uygurs on Thursday celebrated the Nowruz festival in Turkey, marking the first day of spring and the beginning of the year on the Persian calendar.
The Chinese embassy hosted this Nowruz festival celebration, which is also participated by other Turkish citizens. (Turkey-Nowruz festival)